Octociz/Brix were walking down the halls of the CF when a 
transmission came through. He called to the bot who was helping them.

"Did you hear that? We have to go! Maximals are in trouble!"

Octociz/Brix stromed out of the ship and galloped towards where the 
transmission occured at high speed. Out of the corner of their eye, 
they thought they saw two bots: One who looked like a giant bat, and 
another which looked something like a wolf, but not quite. It didn't 
matter thought. They had to get to the battle field and fast! They 
just hoped that Maximal had held on!

______________________________________________________________________

Vulois was putting on finishing touches on the embassy. He still had 
no clue how to contact the smaller groupes, and with all this 
business about kidnapping, he didn't know the chances of having 
success with the big groupes. He just hoped that his friends had not 
gotten into trouble. He then started to cry and smile at the same 
time, realizing that they were not his assistants, but his friends. 
And they were going to do this, one way or another. He hoped that 
this place would be a sanctuary for all those bots terrified of their 
groupes; that wanted peace. Because this place was going to give them 
all what he had promised Battera when he was stuck in that Predacon 
rafter, and she was hunting him: They were going to get as many bots 
as they could, and than go home.

Vulois returned to his work.
